@node "Distribution" "Distribution Rights and Registration"

The Control Centre (CC) has been declared at the current stage as freeware,
which  means  the program can be distributed freely around the world to any
Amiga user.

CC,  as it stands, has had the saving features removed.  This is because CC
is  beta  software,  meaning it could change at any time, also meaning that
the   version   of   CC  you  possess  may  be  out-of-date  and  therefore
incompatible.   Saving is enabled by use of a keyfile, which is sent to you
when you register the program.

                        @{b}@{fg shine}NOTE: Registering is FREE!@{ub}@{fg text}

Upon  registering, you will be sent a keyfile for use with the beta version
of  CC  (via  e-mail)  which  will  allow  saving.  You are not required to
register  the  program  if  you  just  want  to  see  what CC is all about.
Remember  as  with all keyfiles, do not distribute them onto other people -
even your friends!  Each keyfile has a signature allowing easy trace of the
original owner.

@{b}How to Register@{ub}

Please  send  an  e-mail  to  Oondy  at @{fg shine}101330.1207@compuserve.com@{fg text}, putting
