@node "WhatIsCC" "What is CC?"

CC (The Control Centre) is a program designed to make FUBAR as customisable
as possible.  The program has the following features:

  · Entire worlds can be created in CC for play in FUBAR.
  · CC has functions for preparing data files (be it Worlds, objects, etc.)
    to be distributed around other FUBAR players (like uploading onto the
    Internet, or creating level disks).
  · Complete editors for each aspect of the game:
    - World Map Editor
    - Level Editor
    - Sound Effects Editor
    - Cut Scene Editor
    - Image Bank Editor
    - Object, Weapon and Vehicle Editors
  · CC also features a plug-in system allowing additional tools to be
    incorporated.
  · An easy-to-use graphical user interface
  · Works on any Amiga with at least Workbench 2.04.

@{i}BETA  NOTE:   Since  this  is  beta  software at the moment, anything could
happen,  which  means  that  there  will  be  no doubt in this list getting
larger...@{ui}

@endnode

@remark Hey, you need this.  Yes, you do.  No, really.  I insist.

@node "SystemReqs" "System Requirements"

Since  FUBAR,  the game itself, can be run on a standard A500+, the CC does
also.

  · Requires Workbench 2.04 or higher.
  · 1MB of RAM.

Bear  in mind that the CC runs best from a hard disk.  Floppy disks are not
directly  supported,  so you may find yourself doing a little disk-swapping
if you do not have a second disk drive.

If  you  are  using  a  CD32  or playing from a CD-ROM, you will definately
require  a  floppy disk drive or hard disk to save data.  It is impractical
to  save  to  the  non-volitile  RAM on the CD32, and therefore will not be
allowed.

A recommended setup for FUBAR and the CC is as follows:

  · Workbench 3.x
  · 2MB of RAM
  · CD-ROM drive
  · Hard disk
  · AGA chipset or graphics card and a decent monitor

@endnode

