@node "Installation" "Installing CC"

Since  the CC is distributed with the main FUBAR game, it will be necessary
to install it to a medium before you can use it properly.

@{b}INSTALLING FROM FLOPPY DISK@{ub}

The  CC  is compressed in LZH (or LHA) format on the last disk.  There is a
standard  Amiga  Installer  installation  script  on the same disk, so just
double-click it from Workbench or Shell.

Follow  the  on-screen  instructions,  and  it will allow you to install to
another floppy disk or a hard disk.

@{b}INSTALLING FROM CD-ROM@{ub} (CD32 instructions follow)

The CC is available to launch from the CD.  You will need to load Workbench
first.

Double-click  the  CC  icon  in  the  main  (root) directory of the CD from
Workbench  and the CC program icon and related documentation and data files
will be displayed.

Ideally,  it  is  best  installed to a hard disk.  To do so, open your hard
disks  main  directory in Workbench, find somewhere to put it (in the FUBAR
directory,  for example), and click-and-drag the CC directory icon from the
CD onto the destination window.  CC will be installed.

@{b}CD32 NOTES@{ub}

Since  the CD32 version is the same as the CD-ROM version, the CC directory
appears in the main directory of the disk from Workbench as well.  Although
the  CD32  does  not  come  supplied with Workbench, you may not be able to
access it.  You @{i}can@{ui} run the program, thankfully.

  1.  Switch on (or reset) your CD32 with the FUBAR CD in the drive.
  2.  As the game begins to load, @{b}hold down the yellow button.@{ub}
  3.  The CC should shortly follow, instead of the actual game.

Of  course, if you have an SX-1 or SX-32 expansion with a hard disk, follow
the same instructions for installing from a CD-ROM.

@endnode

