@node "WhatIsWorld" "What is a World?"

Essentially, a  World is a collection of @{" objects " link "Object" 0}, @{" vehicles " link "Vehicle" 0}, @{" weapons " link "Weapon" 0},
@{" maps " link "Map" 0},  @{" countries " link "Country" 0},  sounds  and  @{" images " link "Image" 0}  which  make  up  the  whole
worldwide  battlefield  of  which  the  player  must  conquer  in the game.
Everything in the World is connected in some form or other.

In context to the game, the game starts by reading in the World data.  This
is followed by loading the World map image and the countries are drawn upon
it.   Each  player is alotted a certian amount of vehicles and weapons, and
positioned  on  the  World  map.   Various  options  on the World map allow
trading  and  creation of extra vehicles and weapons which are specified in
the World.

When  two players meet and begin a battle, they fight on the map assoicated
with  the setting for the country on the World map.  The map is loaded, the
objects  are placed and the players vehicles are positioned using images to
represent them.  As a battle progresses, various statistics of vehicles and
weapons degrade, until one side no longer exists.

Of  course,  sounds  also  get  played when various events happen, and each
object, vehicle and weapon can have their own animation.

That's  effectively all you really need to know about the overall structure
of a World.

On  a  more  general  scale, each World is part of the Universe (which is a
level disk to you and me).

@endnode

