@node "ProjectMenu" "Project Menus"

@{b}New World@{ub}

Strangely  enough,  this  creates  a  new  @{" World " link "WhatIsWorld" 0}.  It clears any previous
@{" objects " link "Object" 0},  @{" vehicles " link "Vehicle" 0}, @{" weapons " link "Weapon" 0}, sound effects, @{" levels " link "Map" 0}, etc.  which may
be in memory.

If you have just started the CC, you will need do this first before you can
create a World.

@{b}Open World@{ub}

Attempts  to load a @{" World " link "WhatIsWorld" 0} from disk into memory.  All the assoicated data
files which the World needs to load will also be loaded.

@{i}BETA NOTE: At the moment, just the World data is loaded.@{ui}

@{b}Save World@{ub}

Saves  the  current @{" World " link "WhatIsWorld" 0} to disk, using a name previously specified with
@{b}Save World As@{ub}.

If you have not done a @{b}Save As@{ub} before, the CC will write it as "Unnamed".

@{b}Save World As@{ub}

As @{b}Save World@{ub}, but pops up a file requester.

@{b}Revert@{ub}

This will revert to the last saved version of the @{" World " link "WhatIsWorld" 0} in memory.  It is
exact in operation to @{b}Open World@{ub}, but does not bring up a file requester.

@{b}About@{ub}

Displays  program and version information, registered user information, and
some miscellanous messages put in by the programmer :)

@{b}Quit@{ub}

Closes all windows, frees all used memory and finally closes its screen and
shared resources.  The program is then erased from memory.

In other words, the CC is terminated.

@endnode

