@node "ImageBank" "The Image Bank Window"

The   Image   Bank  Window  is  where  you  create  the   images   required
by @{" objects " link "Object" 0}, @{" vehicles " link "Vehicle" 0}  and  @{" weapons " link "Weapon" 0}  during their various states - for
example  an  exploding animation of where the vehicle blows up.  Images are
also used in @{" level maps " link "Map" 0}.

All  images placed in each bank will be accessable by all objects, vehicles
and weapons whilst creating them in their respective editors.  Only certian
images will be accessable in the level map editor.

@{b}General Image Notes@{ub}

 · All images must be 32 by 32 pixels at maximum, whilst 1 by 1 at minimum.
 · All loaded images will be forced to use the same palette.
 · All  images  must be saved as IFF and have no stencial data (if this is
the case, the image will appear corrupt).
 
@{i}BETA NOTE:  If these restrictions are too nasty, just mail me and I'll sort
them  out.   Personally,  there  is nothing wrong with 64x64 images.  Also,
palettes  cannot  be edited or loaded yet - they would need to be remapped,
and  that  is  something I have no knowledge about doing; mail me with your
ideas.   I  was  planning  datatype support on Workbench 3.x for loading of
images  (not  just  for  the  Image  Bank  editor,  tho :) - shall I do it?
Workbench 2.x users will have problems if that's the case...@{ui}
 
@{b}Images to be Used in the Level Map Editor@{ub}

Some  restrictions  apply  on  images  that want to be used in a level map.
These are listed below:

 · The image must be 16 by 16 pixels in size.

The  @{" Level  Map Editor " link "LevelMaps" 0} will show which images are allowed to be used on a
map.  See that for more information.

