@node "WorldMap" "The World Map Editor"

The World Map Editor allows you to set up the World's appearance for the
game  itself.   Here  you  define  what  the  @{" World " link "WhatIsWorld" 0}  looks  like, all the
countries  and  the  owner  settings  of each country.  You can also set up
worldwide parameters, for example weather settings, etc..

@{i}BETA  NOTE:   This  editor  has  many  things yet to be implanted, although
what's there fully works.  Don't expect really good things to be there, but
it will grow over time.@{ui}

When  this  editor  is  invoked,  a  new  screen is opened with the current
representation  of  the  World on it.  Of course, if the World has no world
map then the screen will be blank.

All the editors functions are in the menus.  The menus are as follows:

 @{fg shine}Project@{fg text}
 @{" Clear                      " link "WProjectMenu" 0} - clears the current map to blank
 @{" Revert                     " link "WProjectMenu" 0} - reverts to the last saved map
 @{" Okay                       " link "WProjectMenu" 0} - saves the map and returns to main screen
 @{" Cancel                     " link "WProjectMenu" 0} - cancels the map and returns to main screen

 @{fg shine}Map@{fg text}
 @{" Import Graphic             " link "WMapMenu" 0} - import an image to be the map graphic
 @{" Insert Brush               " link "WMapMenu" 0} - insert a brush onto the map graphic
 @{" Palette                    " link "WMapMenu" 0} - change the palette for the map
 @{" Remove Countries           " link "WMapMenu" 0} - remove all countries from the map
 
 @{fg shine}Country@{fg text}
 @{" Create                     " link "WCountryMenu" 0} - add a country to the World
 @{" Edit                       " link "WCountryMenu" 0} - modify a previously created country
 @{" Delete                     " link "WCountryMenu" 0} - remove a country from the World

 @{fg shine}Options@{fg text}
 @{" Show Countries             " link "WOptionsMenu" 0} - should countries be drawn whilst editing
 @{" Show Owners                " link "WOptionsMenu" 0} - should country owners be shown
 @{" Show Title Bar             " link "WOptionsMenu" 0} - display the screens title bar or not

@endnode

@node "WProjectMenu" "World Editor's Project Menus"

@{b}Clear@{ub}
Clear the World map, and remove all the data from memory.

@{b}Revert@{ub}
This  effectively undoes @{i}all@{ui} the changes you have made to the World map, by
reloading what the World map was from disk.  Of course, if you are creating
the map for the first time, revert will do nothing.

@{b}Okay@{ub}
Keeps  the  changes  to  the World map, and attempts to write them to disk.
This  will write a file called <worldname>.wmp - where "<worldname>" is the
last  name  given  to  the  World from the @{" Save World " link "ProjectMenu" 17} option on the front
screen.    If   you  haven't  saved  the  World  yet,  it  will  be  called
"Unnamed.wmp".

@{i}BETA  NOTE:   Yes,  this  is  a bit funny at the moment when a new World is
being created.  This will all be sorted out in time..  :)@{ui}

@{b}Cancel@{ub}
Forgets the changes and returns to the front screen.

@endnode

@node "WMapMenu" "World Editor's Map Menus"

@{b}Import Graphic@{ub}
See @{" here " link "WMapImportG" 0} for more information about this function.

@{b}Insert Brush@{ub}
This  allows you to "paste" a brush onto the map graphic, previously loaded
with @{b}Import Graphic@{ub}.

Insert  Brush  will  open a file requester, asking you to select a brush to
load.   Once  a  valid image has been loaded, the CC will ask you where you
want  to  place  it.  Simply move the mouse to the position, click the left
mouse button (right to cancel) and there you go.

@{b}Palette@{ub}
This  opens  the  palette  editor.  See @{" here " link "WMapPaletteE" 0} for more information on this
function.

@{b}Remove Countries@{ub}
This will remove all the created countries from the World map.

@{i}BETA  NOTE:   Oddly  enough,  I've  seemed  to  have  forgotten  about this
function!  Erm, just delete them one-by-one at the moment :)@{ui}

@endnode

@node "WMapPaletteE" "Palette Editor - World Map Editor"

The Palette Editor allows you to change the colours used on the World map's
screen.

The user interface looks something like this:

