@node "PlugIn" "What is a Plug-in?"

Many  modern  applications  have  a  feature  with  allows  them to grow to
anyone's needs.  A plug-in allows an application to be extended by adding a
program  in which connects to the main program giving the main program more
features.

For example, you could have a paint package.  If you want the paint package
to read in specific graphics file formats (e.g.  JPEG) for which it doesn't
already  support,  an  external  program  can be "plugged in" to the actual
paint package, giving it the commands it needs to read in a JPEG picture.

It  may sound complex, but really - for the user - it's quite simple.  Copy
a file into a directory, and that's it.

Current plug-ins planned for the CC are as follows:

@{b}Cut Scene Editor@{ub}
This  will  allow  you to create animations which can be played at specific
times during the game.  These add atmosphere to the game, and also give the
player(s) an idea into what's coming next.

This plug-in is being developed by Q-Group.

@{b}World Manager@{ub}
This  is  a  program,  much  like a file-managing utility, but is specially
designed  to organise Worlds generated in the CC.  It can prepare Worlds so
they  can  be  distributed  (via  disk, or the Internet with special Aminet
features)  and  installed on other machines with FUBAR installed.  It has a
full GUI and is very easy-to-use.

This plug-in is being developed by Q-Group.

@endnode

